getAnchorLevel

public int getAnchorLevel()
Indicates the heading level at which anchors of the form &lt;anchor id="additions"/&gt; should be emitted. A level of 0 corresponds to the root of the document, and levels 1-6 correspond to heading levels h1, h2...h6.

The default is -1.

Since:
2.0
See Also:
setAnchorLevel(int)

setHelpPrefix

public void setHelpPrefix(java.lang.String helpPrefix)
the prefix to URLs in the toc.xml, typically the relative path from the plugin to the help files. For example, if the help file is in 'help/index.html' then the help prefix would be 'help'
